description: For sale: $400,000. Colonial meets contemporary in this professionally updated 4BR/4BA STUNNING 2-story with oversized, heated/insulated 3-stall garage & storage shed. This freshly painted home boasts a new maintenance-free deck w/pergola, completely updated LL with new LVP flooring & reclaimed wood planking on walls, updated bathrooms, MF laundry, 4 BRs up, new carpet in BR 2, large master with walk-in closet & a fully updated en suite w/Jacuzzi tub, extensive built-ins throughout, new kitchen faucet, granite & new solid surface counters, hardwood floors, new porcelain & ceramic tile, steel siding, concrete driveway, & landscaped with beautiful perennials. With a wood-burning FP that nicely centers the formal living room, a gas FP & wetbar in LL with a walkout to a new concrete patio, & a classy veranda off family room, this home has been designed for entertainment. Located in prestigious Briar Oakes Estates, this gorgeous colonial is close to shopping, schools, parks/trails & 1-94.

For sale: $274,900. This house boasts 9' ceilings, original breathtaking ornate woodwork, along with hardwood floors, a built-in china hutch and bookcases with leaded glass doors. There are many extras, too numerous to mention! This home is a must see, with its unique windows and architectural design from days gone by. It offers character not seen in homes of today. You won't be disappointed!

For sale: $332,900. Under construction four level conveniently located close to shopping, schools, parks and freeway access. Additional staircase leads from the back of the garage to the third level laundry area. This creates a nice mud room to help keep messes out of your living spaces. The master suite features a spacious walk-in closet and private master bathroom with a linen closet. Second bedroom boasts a walk-in closet as well. Landscape allowance is included in the price.

description: For sale: $449,900. Simply amazing 2.49 acre home! This home has been built,  loved and cared for by its current owners for 25 years.  Massive great room addition & attention to detail, surrounds this beautiful home! This is NOT a drive by...Absolute perfection has gone into all the character, special touches, layout & maintenance. Wonderful massive fireplace showcases the homes vaulted, rustic, great room with wet bar, game room and plenty of easy living and extra entertaining spaces. Open farm style kitchen, Silestone counters, lovely island, huge pantry, eat in kitchen, and separate dining, perfect for large family gatherings. You won't find a better entertaining home, anywhere. Hidden storage behind bookshelf under staircase. The property is tucked in and around Sherburne National Wildlife Refuge, Sand Dunes, and UNCAS Dunes Scientific Nautral Area, creating privacy galore. Big bedrooms, main level master with laundry. 40 x 30 heated Pole Barn.

For sale: $399,000. Gorgeous Mississippi River retreat; two story home with oversized rooms on a level .73 acres with 137' of river frontage. The spacious main level features a large kitchen and two living areas. A large deck off the kitchen/dining area overlooks a nicely landscaped back yard with mature trees, perennial gardens and spectacular river views. The upper level features 3 bedrooms on the same level. Spacious master bedroom with private bath, walk-in closet and private deck. The lower level offers you more living options: Rec room, sauna to relax in, den that could be converted to 4th bedroom and ¾ bath. Insulated 3 stall garage with additional 12x18 workshop. You can even load the fireplace from this space, eliminating the need to bring wood inside. Monticello Schools. NorthStar Commuter Line less than 10 minutes away!

For sale: $299,000. Move-in ready, Mississippi River home with 3 bedrooms and 2 baths.  The main level features a remodeled kitchen with breakfast island and tiled flooring. Extra cabinetry gives you loads of storage options. Newer maintenance free deck off kitchen provides views of the Mississippi River.  Large master with walk-thru bathroom. Double closets for extra storage. Master could be divided to give you a 4th bedroom. Approximately 140+ feet of river frontage on a 1.27 acre lot!  Walkout lower level with a cement patio.  The back yard has many mature trees and perennial gardens. Monticello Schools. Quick access to Hwy 25 and CR 14. Less than 5 minutes to shopping and I-94.

description:
Recently sold: $382,000. Contact the official listing agent, Julie Betzler with Realty Group Inc for the most accurate and up to date information on this amazing property!  Welcome to your new ?stay-cation? golf villa! Located on the Riverwood National 18 Hole Golf Course, is where you?ll find this stunning nearly new 2017 built detached townhome golf villa with all the upgrades!  It is fully finished with 2,438 square feet , a walkout rambler style townhome with main level living (plus finished lower level) and situated on one of the larger lots in this neighborhood, on a culdesac with direct access and back views of Hole 9 and front views of Hole 1! The property is within close proximity to the clubhouse, parks, the Mississippi River, the Albertville Outlet Mall, dining options, conveniences and Hwy 101 and I-94!  Call it home today!!

This home was built in 2017 by local builder Crestwood Homes and includes a covered front entry, beautiful landscaping, irrigated yard and an insulated, heated & epoxied floor 2 car main level garage, plus a convenient tuckunder 3rd stall golf cart garage off the back lower level.  There is also a partially covered main level deck and lower level paver patio, both with golf course views. Home includes gutters, concrete driveway & fully landscaped. 

Walk in from the covered front entry to the welcoming spacious foyer with direct access to the front bedroom/office and main level guest full bathroom.  The main level features an open floor plan with wood floors throughout foyer, kitchen, dining and living room. The kitchen features medium stained cabinetry accented with glass tile backsplash, granite counters, oil rubbed bronze hardware, center angled island, pendant, recessed & under-cabinet lighting, stainless steel appliances including a gas range and a walk-in pantry. Informal dining has sliding glass doors with which leads to the covered deck.  The living room features corner gas fireplace with floor to ceiling stone surround and breath-taking golf course views. The master bedroom has a ceiling fan, neutral carpet, trayed ceiling and a private master bathroom with walk-in tiled shower, tiled floors, double custom vanity with granite tops, natural light window in bath and walk-in closet and separate water closet with pocket door.  The main level living also includes a separate laundry room with front load washer and dryer and built in cabinetry, plus a mudroom off the garage with custom bench seating and coat closet.  All 2 paneled stained doors and white trim throughout. 

The walkout lower level is fully finished with huge family room with 2nd gas fireplace with stone surround, separate dedicated home gym area with French doors, a 3rd bedroom, a full bathroom, a very spacious mechanical room with loads of storage area and an awesome golf cart garage (or storage area or workshop area?you choose!)

description: Recently sold: $258,500. This home is a Real Estate Owned (REO)/Post Foreclosure. Once a lender has foreclosed on a property it is soon put up for public auction. If bids fall short of the asking price the bank will buy back the home and attempt to sell it on the open market. However, lenders are not real estate agents, meaning that they will often accept offers 30 to 60 percent less than market value!

Recently sold: $286,500. Total remodel all rooms 2017 and 2018. Please focus on new pictures. 98% of new products, merchandise and services purchased from The Home Depot.  Pictures represent what is being remodeled present Time.  We have many new remodel projects to complete in 2018 at 201 Mississippi Drive.  

Serenity.  Gorgeous river front home. Main level Master suite with Jacuzzi tub. Beautiful open floor plan with views of the Mississippi through large picture windows.  
Open House, 8 am - 4 pm, Saturday, February 3, 2018. Sunday, February 11, 2018, at 4:00 pm is the deadline for all buyers to make their best offer, and their best earnest money offer.  When we come to terms on our home, I will contact my lawyer.  The new buyer will contact their agent, either their lawyer or their financial institution.  
Please email, richthurman1@gmail.com...for an appointment to see our home.  The new owners will take possession at 2:00 pm, Saturday, May 5, 2018.  We will work with a buyers real estate agent at this time.

NEITHER the seller nor the buyer benefits from a bidding war on a home for sale. Buyers pre-approved for a mortgage loan are almost as good as a cash offering. Please bring your bank's pre-qualification loan paperwork with you for your viewing.

We feel the following concepts will benefit both the buyer and the seller.  Our goal is to give all parties involved an even playing field.
1. Integrity rules. We will not accept the highest bid, then discard the rest. We will ask all potential buyers for their best offer...2. We will counter your offer.  We will not reject your offer.  Ex: You and your spouse give us a bid on a Friday afternoon.  We tell you we're not going to respond to your offer until the very next Monday.  Please understand...The integrity...we have other people who want to view our home on Saturday and Sunday...3. Cash payment for our home is neat, clean, and quick for both the seller and buyer.  When cash is offered, we will not accept a contingency bid based upon the buyer selling their home. Nonnegotiable.  The seller will not waive contingencies such as A. our homes inspection by a licensed, insured inspector.  The buyer pays for the inspection.  The seller pays for situations that the inspector presents.  B.  All paperwork is subject to my lawyer's approval and review. C.  Your bank's mortgage approval...4. For all offers, cash or otherwise, we will review the proposed terms...5. Appraisal requirements.  Mortgage companies may not be willing to lend the difference if an appraisal comes in below the purchase price, unless the buyer is willing to make up the difference out of pocket...6. The seller will ask how much earnest money each bidder is offering.  Earnest money goes to an agent that represents the the seller.  Earnest money is not a down payment.  It is money held in escrow in a non interest bearing account by my lawyer.  It is used to make sure the buyer does not back out of the sale of the home at the last minute...7. We will work together to find a time that is mutually beneficially to both the seller and the buyer for a common closing time.
